WEBVTT

00:08.083 --> 00:10.884
[ Munching ]

00:10.886 --> 00:12.885
-[ Slurps ]
-Huh?

00:12.954 --> 00:14.553
I was just
sipping my coffee.

00:14.623 --> 00:15.688
Oh.

00:15.757 --> 00:17.691
[ Munching ]

00:17.693 --> 00:19.159
[ Slurps ]

00:19.161 --> 00:22.462
[ Both continue slurping
and munching rhythmically ]

00:33.375 --> 00:35.041
[ Both laugh ]

00:35.043 --> 00:38.177
[ BMO laughs ]

00:38.246 --> 00:41.113
I am also excited
about today.

00:41.183 --> 00:42.649
Oh, yeah?

00:42.651 --> 00:46.386
Today is the first day
of my new job.

00:46.454 --> 00:47.921
What's your new job, BMO?

00:47.989 --> 00:49.589
Yeah, are you a spy?

00:49.657 --> 00:51.524
You know,
'cause of the overcoat?

00:51.593 --> 00:53.793
I'm a door-to-door
salesman.

00:53.862 --> 00:54.927
-Oh.
-Oh.

00:54.996 --> 00:56.396
What are you selling?

00:56.464 --> 00:58.598
I've got
so many great things.

00:58.667 --> 01:01.001
Like for
the man about town,

01:01.069 --> 01:02.602
this piece of lint.

01:02.671 --> 01:04.003
I'll take it.

01:04.072 --> 01:06.539
Hooray! My first sale!

01:06.607 --> 01:08.875
That'll be
four doubloons.

01:08.943 --> 01:10.877
Can I pay you later?

01:10.945 --> 01:13.813
Mm, the customer
is always right!

01:13.882 --> 01:16.549
Good attitude, BMO.

01:16.551 --> 01:18.618
Well, gentlemen...

01:18.687 --> 01:20.854
got to chop that wood.

01:25.894 --> 01:29.762
♪♪

01:29.831 --> 01:31.031
[ Whispering ]
It's Ice King.

01:31.099 --> 01:34.033
[ Whispering ]
I know.

01:34.102 --> 01:35.435
Oh!

01:39.707 --> 01:42.241
Okay, wish me luck, fellas,
even though I don't need --

01:42.310 --> 01:43.576
-Aah!
-Aah!

01:43.645 --> 01:45.712
[ Thud ]
[ Both giggle ]

01:45.780 --> 01:48.647
-Aw.
-Aw.

01:48.717 --> 01:50.850
Ice King:
Boy, this is great, huh?

01:50.918 --> 01:52.918
You and me
out in the fresh air?

01:52.988 --> 01:55.121
Now, the key
to being a tip-top salesman

01:55.189 --> 01:57.257
is to get the ol' foot
in the door.

01:57.259 --> 01:59.459
Bodies don't talk,
Ice King.

01:59.527 --> 02:01.594
Well, mine does.

02:01.663 --> 02:03.863
Okay, then.
If I say "My feet hurt,"

02:03.932 --> 02:05.598
you can go "Woof woof."

02:05.667 --> 02:07.267
That's my dogs barking.

02:07.269 --> 02:10.670
BMO, I think we're gonna make
an unbeatable team.

02:10.739 --> 02:13.273
Yeah, yeah! Let's go! Let's go!
Let's go! Let's go!

02:13.275 --> 02:14.607
[ Laughs ]

02:17.612 --> 02:21.747
Tree Trunks: "Chapter 3 --
No Time For Sleeping.

02:21.817 --> 02:24.083
Elizabeth's heart was racing

02:24.152 --> 02:27.554
like a water mill
after spring thaw.

02:27.556 --> 02:30.156
She knew her enemies
were coming for her,

02:30.225 --> 02:31.757
but when?

02:31.827 --> 02:34.561
Suddenly, there was a knock
at the door."

02:34.629 --> 02:36.562
[ Knock on door ]
Oh!

02:36.631 --> 02:39.899
Tree Trunks:
Oh. Oh, my goodness. [ Groans ]

02:39.968 --> 02:41.634
Someone's at the door.

02:41.703 --> 02:44.170
That's all.

02:44.239 --> 02:45.572
Hello.

02:45.574 --> 02:47.239
Tree Trunks,
how are your children?

02:47.309 --> 02:51.177
Can you believe
this weather?

02:51.245 --> 02:53.847
So polite.

02:53.849 --> 02:57.117
Please, please come in.

02:57.185 --> 02:59.719
You have a lovely home.

02:59.721 --> 03:01.721
Here, have
some apple pie.

03:01.723 --> 03:04.123
Oh, thank you.

03:04.125 --> 03:06.125
Now, what
can I do for you?

03:06.127 --> 03:09.929
Oh, well, I'd like to show you
what I'm selling today.

03:09.998 --> 03:11.597
[ Grunts ]

03:11.666 --> 03:14.601
♪♪

03:17.672 --> 03:20.206
Okay, we have
a broken branch,

03:20.275 --> 03:21.874
a half-eaten sandwich --

03:21.943 --> 03:23.676
oh, another ball of lint.

03:23.745 --> 03:24.877
Another?

03:24.946 --> 03:26.880
These are selling
like red hots.

03:26.948 --> 03:30.817
A dust bunny -- That's like
a cage-free ball of lint.

03:30.819 --> 03:32.218
A doll's head,

03:32.287 --> 03:35.955
and a little velvet bag,
tied tight at the top.

03:36.024 --> 03:38.357
I'll take the branch.

03:38.426 --> 03:41.160
My loose cash
is up there

03:41.229 --> 03:43.029
in the flower jar.

03:43.097 --> 03:45.898
Help yourself.

03:45.967 --> 03:47.767
Ice King: Ohh!

03:55.643 --> 03:58.311
[ Jar clunks ]
[ Laughs ]

03:58.313 --> 04:01.581
[ Both laugh ]

04:01.649 --> 04:02.849
You have a lovely home.

04:02.917 --> 04:04.918
-Aah!
-Whoa!

04:04.986 --> 04:06.653
What'd you buy,
honey bunch?

04:06.721 --> 04:07.987
A branch.

04:08.056 --> 04:10.389
Huh.

04:10.458 --> 04:11.924
Huh? Oh.

04:11.993 --> 04:15.261
Ah, Tree Trunks,
you're a financial genius.

04:15.329 --> 04:16.729
[ BMO laughs ]

04:16.797 --> 04:19.199
I can't believe
we unloaded that branch.

04:19.267 --> 04:21.801
It wasn't even
our best one.

04:21.803 --> 04:24.270
Oh, my.
Shield my eyes from the sun.

04:24.339 --> 04:25.738
Ice King: Why?

04:25.807 --> 04:28.208
Because I think I see
our next customer.

04:30.879 --> 04:32.612
Those nuts could be ours.

04:32.680 --> 04:36.349
Excuse me, little boy!

04:36.351 --> 04:38.017
How are your children?!

04:38.086 --> 04:40.686
Ice King, duck.

04:40.755 --> 04:41.888
Jump.

04:41.956 --> 04:43.756
Right.
Right again.

04:43.825 --> 04:46.092
[ Laughs ]
Left.

04:46.160 --> 04:47.893
Jump, jump.

04:47.963 --> 04:52.231
♪♪

04:52.300 --> 04:54.367
Left. Right.

04:54.369 --> 04:56.903
Left.

04:56.905 --> 04:58.905
Ice King,
you're doing so good.

04:58.973 --> 05:01.107
You have not
bumped into anything.

05:01.175 --> 05:04.644
BMO,
where's the customer?

05:04.712 --> 05:06.179
Oh, no.
I was so excited

05:06.247 --> 05:10.316
about you not bumping into
anything, I lost the customer.

05:10.385 --> 05:13.253
Ice King,
I think we are lost.

05:13.321 --> 05:14.754
[ Animal howls ]

05:18.927 --> 05:20.727
Look.

05:20.795 --> 05:22.261
-A house.
-All I see

05:22.263 --> 05:24.931
is the inside of this coat.

05:24.933 --> 05:27.066
And...stop.

05:27.068 --> 05:29.402
Knock politely.

05:29.470 --> 05:31.403
[ Footsteps ]

05:31.473 --> 05:33.373
[ Hinges creak ]

05:38.746 --> 05:41.347
Mysterious sentinel,
you have a lovely home.

05:41.349 --> 05:42.748
[ Whispering ]
Turn.

05:42.817 --> 05:44.017
[ Normal voice ]
How are your children?

05:44.019 --> 05:45.685
[ Gasps ]

05:45.753 --> 05:48.721
♪♪

05:55.897 --> 05:57.330
Hello.

06:00.969 --> 06:03.703
I'm a door-to-door salesman,
ma'am.

06:03.771 --> 06:05.371
[ Ice King coughs ]

06:05.373 --> 06:08.774
[ Chuckling ] Oh,
excuse my indigestion.

06:08.843 --> 06:09.842
Ouch!

06:09.911 --> 06:12.244
I have some wonderful
new products,

06:12.313 --> 06:15.114
like, uh,
this ball of lint.

06:15.182 --> 06:17.383
No, wait,
this is the dust bunny. Uh...

06:17.385 --> 06:20.353
Oh, oh!
I know -- this velvet bag.

06:23.391 --> 06:27.527
Did I mention
that it contains Finn's teeth?

06:27.529 --> 06:29.796
[ Ax clatters ]
Please, let's go in the parlor,

06:29.798 --> 06:33.799
where we can be
more comfortable.

06:33.868 --> 06:36.402
And you're sure
these are Finn's teeth?

06:36.471 --> 06:38.270
-Yes.
-The same Finn

06:38.339 --> 06:40.406
who serves Princess Bubblegum,
obstructs my plans,

06:40.475 --> 06:42.475
and plagues my thoughts?

06:42.543 --> 06:43.476
Yes.

06:43.544 --> 06:46.079
Finn the human's teeth.

06:46.081 --> 06:48.881
That's a BMO guarantee.

06:48.949 --> 06:50.349
Ice King: [ Whispering ]
Psst! Does Finn know

06:50.351 --> 06:52.285
you have his teeth?
Because I don't think --

06:52.353 --> 06:55.154
[ Whispering ] Hey!
I'm trying to close a sale here.

06:55.156 --> 06:57.290
I hope
you accept silver.

06:57.292 --> 07:00.159
I can pay you
immediately.

07:00.228 --> 07:02.228
Yes, my pretties.

07:04.365 --> 07:07.100
Poor, little guy. Still
wearing out the shoe leather

07:07.168 --> 07:11.104
trying to make just one more
lousy sale before coming home.

07:11.172 --> 07:14.040
He'll feel better after we have
a little party for him.

07:14.108 --> 07:15.908
Still, it's tough
seeing your kid

07:15.977 --> 07:18.444
get his heart set on doing
something he really sucks at.

07:18.513 --> 07:20.146
[ Door opens ]

07:22.316 --> 07:25.851
Hello, boys.
Meet the salesman of the year.

07:25.920 --> 07:27.987
Or maybe of the decade.

07:28.055 --> 07:29.522
The Chinese food is on me.

07:29.590 --> 07:31.924
I mean,
check out the loot.

07:31.993 --> 07:33.993
[ Whispering ]
It's real.

07:33.995 --> 07:36.862
What the heck did you sell
to get this silver goblet?

07:36.931 --> 07:40.466
Just a line of smooth talk
and pipe dreams.

07:40.535 --> 07:42.935
Oh, and a set
of human baby teeth.

07:43.003 --> 07:46.539
Where did you even get
a set of human baby teeth?

07:46.607 --> 07:48.541
Human baby teeth!!

07:48.543 --> 07:51.411
♪♪

07:54.482 --> 07:56.081
BMO!

07:56.151 --> 08:00.286
Branches and lint
are moving like cray, Jake.

08:00.354 --> 08:03.021
Oh, sure,
I sold your baby teeth.

08:03.091 --> 08:05.357
I could sell
any part of you.

08:05.426 --> 08:07.025
These were, like,
the only things I had left

08:07.095 --> 08:10.162
from when I was a little kid.

08:10.231 --> 08:12.031
Hey, you know what?
We'll just go buy back

08:12.099 --> 08:14.433
those little pearly whites.
I'm sure whoever bought them

08:14.502 --> 08:16.569
is like, "Why did I buy
these things?"

08:16.571 --> 08:18.304
What possible use
could some guy have

08:18.306 --> 08:20.372
for a set of human baby teeth?

08:20.441 --> 08:23.976
Unless he's an evil sorcerer
or a mad scientist.

08:24.045 --> 08:26.512
He wasn't a mad scientist,
was he?

08:26.581 --> 08:30.182
Well...
[ Pounding on door ]

08:30.251 --> 08:33.186
♪♪

08:39.527 --> 08:41.326
[ Shrieks ]

08:41.396 --> 08:42.661
Stay back, baby Finns.

08:42.730 --> 08:43.863
Aah!

08:43.931 --> 08:45.464
[ Both scream ]

08:45.533 --> 08:46.899
[ Groans ]

08:48.603 --> 08:50.603
[ Grunts ]

08:50.605 --> 08:53.539
They're made out of some kind
of hard tooth-like material.

08:53.541 --> 08:55.007
Ouch. Ouch!

08:55.009 --> 08:56.943
Ice King,
freeze these nightmare babies.

08:57.011 --> 08:58.944
I'm not allowed
to wear my crown.

08:59.013 --> 09:00.546
It's against
BMO's dress code.

09:00.615 --> 09:02.949
Just don't let them
climb into your mouth!

09:03.017 --> 09:04.550
[ Groaning ]

09:04.619 --> 09:07.353
Hey, there, bitey boys.
Get off of there.

09:07.421 --> 09:09.489
[ Groaning ]

09:09.557 --> 09:11.957
Where's your baby manners?
Eek.

09:12.026 --> 09:15.294
Hmm.
Maybe I sold too well.

09:15.362 --> 09:18.097
Ice King:
Hey, you're a great salesman.

09:18.099 --> 09:20.433
Evil babies are not
a problem for you.

09:20.501 --> 09:22.501
They're an opportunity.

09:22.570 --> 09:24.036
Yeah.

09:24.105 --> 09:25.304
Where did I put those --

09:25.306 --> 09:27.240
Oh, here they are.

09:27.308 --> 09:31.377
Gentlemen, could I interest you
in a couple of sledgehammers?

09:31.445 --> 09:35.181
Perfect for smashing through
minerals or composites.

09:35.249 --> 09:37.382
-I'll take one.
-Me, too!

09:37.452 --> 09:39.051
Great decision.

09:39.053 --> 09:43.389
♪♪

09:43.457 --> 09:45.124
[ Poof! ]

09:48.997 --> 09:51.297
A little tap
is all it takes.

09:53.535 --> 09:56.335
These baby-smashing hammers
are great.

09:56.404 --> 09:59.005
[ Whacking continues ]

10:03.011 --> 10:05.211
I'm sorry
I caused such a mess.

10:05.213 --> 10:08.013
It's very bad
for business.

10:08.082 --> 10:10.283
Well, time
to call it day.

10:14.422 --> 10:16.389
The ice man leaveth.

10:18.426 --> 10:20.159
Hey, wait.

10:20.161 --> 10:23.696
See you tomorrow...
partner.

10:23.764 --> 10:25.631
Until tomorrow.

10:25.699 --> 10:27.767
Yeah, you're not
doing this tomorrow.

10:27.769 --> 10:30.403
[ Whistling ]

10:32.573 --> 10:36.175
Hmm. In retrospect, the attack
would have worked much better

10:36.243 --> 10:38.377
were they not baby teeth.

10:38.446 --> 10:39.579
[ Clears throat ]

10:44.719 --> 10:48.787
♪ Come along with me

10:48.856 --> 10:52.358
♪ And the butterflies and bees

10:55.663 --> 10:58.030
This party is so crazy!
